Key Match Events: Namibia needed 18 runs off 18 balls with seven wickets in hand but Oman managed to push the game to a Super Over.
Mehran Khan delivered a wicket maiden in the 17th over.
Mehran Khan took crucial wickets in the final over, including Frylinck and Green.
Wiese hit a six in the 18th over to keep Namibia in the game.
The match ended in a tie, leading to a Super Over which Namibia eventually won.
Post-Match Reflections: O'Brien commented that it was the wrong call to give Bilal the Super Over instead of Mehran.
